properties.abstract: This loop offers a visit to the Montagne du Droit south of Tramelan, running through pastures, passing beneath the wind turbines and featuring an impressive view of the Franches-Montagnes and Chasseral. Stops can be made at mountain pasture restaurants.
properties.description:
Starting from Tramelan station, this tour rises gradually and gently through forests and pastures towards La Tanne. It then winds its way around typical Jura farms to reach the ridge. Once on the ridge, the route becomes easier and there is a 360° panoramic view: the Franches-Montagnes, Chasseral, the Valley of Saint-Imier and Mont-Crosin with its wind turbines.

Here, amid the wooded pastures, you are sure to feel a sense of fulfilment and calm. To return to Tramelan, simply release the brakes and allow the pleasant descent to begin.
